  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-03-18",
    "date": "2021-12-03T22:13:05Z",
    "text": "Stopping Illicit Trafficking Act of 2021 or the SIFT Act of 2021\n\nThis bill adds five fentanyl analogues and the entire category of fentanyl-related substances to schedule I of the Controlled Substances Act. A schedule I controlled substance is a drug, substance, or chemical that has a high potential for abuse; has no currently accepted medical value; and is subject to regulatory controls and administrative, civil, and criminal penalties under the Controlled Substances Act.\n\nThe bill also creates a process to remove from schedule I certain fentanyl-related substances that do not have a high potential for abuse."
  },
